
[1]stedfastness

   STEADFASTNESS, STEDFASTNESS, n.

   1. Firmness of standing; fixedness in place.

   2. Firmness of mind or purpose; fixedness in principle; constancy;
   resolution; as the stedfastness of faith. He adhered to his opinions
   with steadfastness.
